Un-rarefied Plots

first Im going to read in the un rarefied no singlton data

metadata<-read_q2metadata("metadata.txt") # must contain q2:types in second line
SVs<-read_qza("table.qza")$data
taxonomy<-read_qza("taxonomy.qza")$data %>% parse_taxonomy()

SVs <- as.data.frame(SVs)

remove any samples (controls/blanks) that you dont want to see in the plots

drops <- c("16S-46", "16S-PB", "16S-CB", "X16S-FB") # to drop all blanks use c("16S-46","16S-FB", "16S-RLB", "16S-SB", "16S-PB")
SVs <- SVs[ , !(names(SVs) %in% drops)]
metadata<- metadata %>% 
  filter(`Keep`=="Yes") # to drpo all banks used Keep2

for some reason after parse taxonomy d__ remain in the kingdom column, so Ive removed it manually

taxonomy$Kingdom <- gsub("d__", "",taxonomy$Kingdom)

#remove repetitive Marinimicrobia_(SAR406_clade); M label
taxonomy$Phylum <-  gsub("_(SAR406_clade)", "", taxonomy$Phylum, fixed = TRUE) #fixed true is to stope there being an issue with special charcters
taxonomy$Class <-  gsub("Marinimicrobia_(SAR406_clade)", "SAR406_clade", taxonomy$Class, fixed = TRUE)
taxonomy$Order <-  gsub("Marinimicrobia_(SAR406_clade)", "SAR406_clade", taxonomy$Order, fixed = TRUE)
taxonomy$Family <-  gsub("Marinimicrobia_(SAR406_clade)", "SAR406_clade", taxonomy$Family, fixed = TRUE)
taxonomy$Genus <-  gsub("Marinimicrobia_(SAR406_clade)", "SAR406_clade", taxonomy$Genus, fixed = TRUE)


## Species Plots
#join SVs and taxonomy with summaries at a species level
taxasums<-summarize_taxa(SVs, taxonomy)$Species


# produce heatmap with samples grouped by the type of preservative
taxa_heatmap(taxasums, metadata, "Preservative")

# produce a taxa barplot with samples grouped by preservative
taxa_barplot(taxasums, metadata, "Preservative")

Genus Plots

taxasumsgenus<-summarize_taxa(SVs, taxonomy)$Genus

taxa_heatmap(taxasumsgenus, metadata, "Preservative")

taxa_barplot(taxasumsgenus, metadata, "Preservative")

Remove Eukaryota

Im now removing Eukaryota from taxasums and producing the same plots with Eukaryotes in the data

taxsums_noEuk<- taxasums[!grepl("Eukaryota.*", row.names(taxasums)),]

taxa_heatmap(taxsums_noEuk, metadata, "Preservative")

taxa_barplot(taxsums_noEuk, metadata, "Preservative")

and without Eukaryota by genus

taxsumsgenus_noEuk<- taxasumsgenus[!grepl("Eukaryota.*", row.names(taxasumsgenus)),]

taxa_heatmap(taxsumsgenus_noEuk, metadata, "Preservative")

now Im having a look at the rarefied to 50922 data without Eukaryota

metadata<-read_q2metadata("no-blanks-metadata.txt") # must contain q2:types in second line
SVs<-read_qza("rarefied_table_no_singleton.qza")$data
taxonomy<-read_qza("taxonomy.qza")$data %>% parse_taxonomy()

SVs <- as.data.frame(SVs)
drops <- "16S-46"
SVs <- SVs[ , !(names(SVs) %in% drops)]
#metadata<- metadata %>% 
#  filter(`Keep`=="Yes")

taxonomy$Kingdom <- gsub("d__", "",taxonomy$Kingdom)

#remove repetitive Marinimicrobia_(SAR406_clade); M label
taxonomy$Phylum <-  gsub("_(SAR406_clade)", "", taxonomy$Phylum, fixed = TRUE) #fixed true is to stope there being an issue with special charcters
taxonomy$Class <-  gsub("Marinimicrobia_(SAR406_clade)", "SAR406_clade", taxonomy$Class, fixed = TRUE)
taxonomy$Order <-  gsub("Marinimicrobia_(SAR406_clade)", "SAR406_clade", taxonomy$Order, fixed = TRUE)
taxonomy$Family <-  gsub("Marinimicrobia_(SAR406_clade)", "SAR406_clade", taxonomy$Family, fixed = TRUE)
taxonomy$Genus <-  gsub("Marinimicrobia_(SAR406_clade)", "SAR406_clade", taxonomy$Genus, fixed = TRUE)

Species Plots

taxasums<-summarize_taxa(SVs, taxonomy)$Species

# removing Eukaryota from taxasums

ggsave("heatmap_rarefied50922_species_noEuk.pdf", height=4, width=8, device="pdf") # save a PDF 4 inches by 8 inches
